"(1) (i) The hum of the ’s central spire reverberated through Levi’s bones, a low-frequency pulse that seemed to sync with his own heartbeat as he moved through the sterile corridors. Fluorescent lights cast a cold blue glow over the polished metal floors, reflecting off the glass walls that curved upward into the misty expanse beyond.\n(2) Every so often, the automated climate system vented mist, creating ghostly halos that danced over the security monitors.\n(3) (ii) His assignment had been routine: monitoring cryo-pod containment systems on the lower decks.\n(4) The facility’s purpose was clear—preserving genetic samples and experimental subjects in deep stasis for future revival.\n(5) Yet even in this clinical environment, Levi found his attention drifting to the subtle vibrations in the floor, the faint metallic creaks that sometimes heralded trouble.\n(6) (iii) Today, however, the monitors flashed red in a way that was impossible to ignore. Hydra Cloud Facility.\n(7) A klaxon, sharp and synthetic, pierced the ambient hum. July 25, 2224. witnessed a cryo-pod integrity breach.\n(8) He spun toward the bank of cryo-pods lining the observation bay, his breath catching as the warning siren repeated: “POD INTEGRITY BREACH—SECTOR 7.” The red warning lights flooded the panel, casting jagged shadows across the faces of the silent, motionless pods.\n(9) (iv) He sprinted down the corridor, boots echoing against the reinforced deck, past rows of humming servers and the ever-present surveillance drones that tracked every movement.\n(10) The air was thick with the scent of ozone and ant. Levi Rodriguez."